metadata.name: Entry
metadata.description:
Entry

An individual entry in a log.

examples.code:
require "gcloud"

gcloud = Gcloud.new
logging = gcloud.logging
entry = logging.entries.first

metadata.name: initialize
metadata.description: Create an empty Entry object.

metadata.name: log_name
metadata.description:
The resource name of the log to which this log entry belongs. The format of the name is projects/<project-id>/logs/<log-id>. e.g. projects/my-projectid/logs/syslog and projects/1234567890/logs/library.googleapis.com%2Fbook_log

The log ID part of resource name must be less than 512 characters long and can only include the following characters: upper and lower case alphanumeric characters: [A-Za-z0-9]; and punctuation characters: forward-slash (/), underscore (_), hyphen (-), and period (.). Forward-slash (/) characters in the log ID must be URL-encoded.

metadata.name: log_name=
metadata.description:
The resource name of the log to which this log entry belongs. The format of the name is projects/<project-id>/logs/<log-id>. e.g. projects/my-projectid/logs/syslog and projects/1234567890/logs/library.googleapis.com%2Fbook_log

The log ID part of resource name must be less than 512 characters long and can only include the following characters: upper and lower case alphanumeric characters: [A-Za-z0-9]; and punctuation characters: forward-slash (/), underscore (_), hyphen (-), and period (.). Forward-slash (/) characters in the log ID must be URL-encoded.

metadata.name: resource
metadata.description: The monitored resource associated with this log entry. Example: a log entry that reports a database error would be associated with the monitored resource designating the particular database that reported the error.

metadata.name: timestamp
metadata.description: The time the event described by the log entry occurred. If omitted, Cloud Logging will use the time the log entry is written.

metadata.name: timestamp=
metadata.description: The time the event described by the log entry occurred. If omitted, Cloud Logging will use the time the log entry is written.

metadata.name: severity
metadata.description: The severity of the log entry. The default value is DEFAULT.

metadata.name: severity=
metadata.description: The severity of the log entry. The default value is DEFAULT.

metadata.name: default?
metadata.description: Helper method to determine if the severity is DEFAULT

metadata.name: debug?
metadata.description: Helper method to determine if the severity is DEBUG

metadata.name: info?
metadata.description: Helper method to determine if the severity is INFO

metadata.name: notice?
metadata.description: Helper method to determine if the severity is NOTICE

metadata.name: warning?
metadata.description: Helper method to determine if the severity is WARNING

metadata.name: error?
metadata.description: Helper method to determine if the severity is ERROR

metadata.name: critical?
metadata.description: Helper method to determine if the severity is CRITICAL

metadata.name: alert?
metadata.description: Helper method to determine if the severity is ALERT

metadata.name: emergency?
metadata.description: Helper method to determine if the severity is EMERGENCY

metadata.name: insert_id
metadata.description: A unique ID for the log entry. If you provide this field, the logging service considers other log entries in the same log with the same ID as duplicates which can be removed. If omitted, Cloud Logging will generate a unique ID for this log entry.

metadata.name: insert_id=
metadata.description: A unique ID for the log entry. If you provide this field, the logging service considers other log entries in the same log with the same ID as duplicates which can be removed. If omitted, Cloud Logging will generate a unique ID for this log entry.

metadata.name: labels
metadata.description: A set of user-defined data that provides additional information about the log entry.

metadata.name: labels=
metadata.description: A set of user-defined data that provides additional information about the log entry.

metadata.name: payload
metadata.description: The log entry payload, represented as either a string, a hash (JSON), or a hash (protocol buffer).

metadata.name: payload=
metadata.description: The log entry payload, represented as either a string, a hash (JSON), or a hash (protocol buffer).

metadata.name: http_request
metadata.description: Information about the HTTP request associated with this log entry, if applicable.

metadata.name: operation
metadata.description: Information about an operation associated with the log entry, if applicable.
